Please answer the below core-java Questions:

What is programing language?
A. It is a set of instructions used to execute commands on a computer with various results.
What jdk contains or composed of and define each components?
A. The Runtime Interpreter runs Java bytecodes. The compiler compiles code into a .class file which is
machine readable. The .class file is run through a Java virtual machine where it is executed.
What is IDE?
A. Integrated development environment is software where you can write and run codes.
What are the IDEs available in the market to support java?
A. Eclipse, Intellij, Android studio, etc.
Explain the entire java life cycle.
A. The Runtime Interpreter runs Java bytecodes. The compiler compiles code into a .class file which is
   machine readable. The .class file is run through a Java virtual machine where it is executed.
what is class?
A. Java class is the blueprint for an object.
What is object?
A. Objects are instances of a class.
What is the entry point of an application?
A. That would be the main method.
Why main is static?
A. Because main is invoked by jvm before objects are created. Being static lets it be directly invoked by the class.
Which class is the superclass of all classes?
A. java.lang.object is the superclass.
What is difference between path and classpath variables?
A. Path is the environment variable where we specify the locations of binaries and classpath is
the path for Java application where the classes you compiled will be available.
What is the difference between an Interface and Abstract class?
A. An interface is an empty shell while abstract class looks like a interface but they are actual classes.
Can you make an Object from an Interface and Abstract class ? if not how do you use it ?
A.No you can't make an object from interface or abstract class.
what is Access Specifier?
A. The access specifier is used to determine the visibility of methods and variables.
What is OOP ? Define each feature of java OOP.
A. OOP is object oriented programming. This refers to abstraction, encapsulation, inheritance, and polymorphism.
What is Java Package and which package is imported by default?
A. Java package organizes java classes into namespaces and java.lang package is imported by default.
What is API? Name list of API that you have used so far.
A. Application programming interface is basically a set of routines, protocols, and tools for
building software applications.
Does java support multiple inheritance, explain why or why not?
A. No it does not.
What is method overloading and when it happens?
A. This when the same method uses a different signature and it happens within a class.
Explain exceptions in java and how to handle it.
A. An exception occurs during the execution of a program and is a disruption that interrupts the flow of the
programs instructions.
What is static keyword in java? How it has been used in variables and methods ?
A. Static is a member of a class that is not associated with an instance of a class.
What is final and how it has been used variables and methods?
A. Final is used with variables to specify that it's value should not be changed.
What is final, finally and finalize?
A. Final is used with variables to specify that it's value should not be changed. Finally wil execute important code
whether the exception is handled or not and finalize is used for clean up process before the object is garbage
is collected.
What is a constructor ?
A. It is used to initialize a class.
Can we have multiple constructors in a class?
A. Yes we can.
If we don't have a constructor declared, what is called during the object creation?
A. A default empty constructor will be generated if you don't give one.
What is "this" keyword in java ?
A. It represents instance of a class.
What is "super" keyword in java? How many possible way can you use?
A. This keyword is used to access members of a super class by the extended class.
What is JVM stand for ?
A. Java Virtual Machine
Is JVM platform independent?
A. No JVM is platform dependent.
